{"title_page": "Rinspeed", "text_new": "{{Primary sources|date=February 2008}}\n[[File:Rinspeed Logo.jpg|thumb|right|400px|Rinspeed Logo]]\n\n'''Rinspeed''' is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[List of automobile manufacturers|automobile manufacturer]] and [[Car tuning|tuning]] designer. It specialises in restoring classic cars, and tuning and modifying modern cars such as [[Porsche]]s and [[Subaru]]s.  Since 1991, they have also designed exotic [[concept car|concept]] and special vehicles for the [[Geneva Motor Show]] and other car shows each year, but do not enter into production.\n\nRinspeed was founded in 1979 by Frank Rinderknecht.\n\n==Concept cars==\n[[File:Rinspeed sQuba (TWB 2008).jpg|thumb|sQuba concept car at the Tuning World Bodensee 2008]] \n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* [[Rinspeed Speed-Art|Speed-Art]] (1992)\n* [[Rinspeed Veleno|Veleno]] (1993)\n* Cyan (1994)\n* Roadster R + SC-R (1995)\n* [[Rinspeed Yello Talbo|Yello Talbo]] (1996)\n* [[Rinspeed Mono Ego|Mono Ego]] (1997)\n* E-Go Rocket (1998)\n* X-Trem (1999)\n* [[Rinspeed Tatooo.com|Tatooo.com]] (2000)\n* [[Rinspeed Rone|R<sup>one</sup>]] (2001)\n* [[Rinspeed Presto|Presto]] (2002)\n* [[Rinspeed Bedouin|Bedouin]] (2003)\n* [[Rinspeed Splash|Splash]] (2004)\n* Chopster (2005)\n* [[Rinspeed Senso|Senso]] (2005)\n* [[Rinspeed zaZen|zaZen]] (2006)\n* [[Rinspeed eXasis|eXasis]] (2007)\n* [[Rinspeed Le Mans 600|Le Mans 600]] (2007)\n* [[Rinspeed sQuba|sQuba]] (2008)\n* [[Rinspeed iChange|iChange]] (2009)\n* [[Rinspeed UC?|UC?]] (2010)<ref>{{Webarchiv | url=http://www.rinspeed.com/pages/cars/uc/prd-uc.htm | wayback=20110612082015 | text=Rinspeed vereint Auto, Bahn und Web in einem neuartigen Mobilit\u00e4tskonzept}} (Herstellerseite)</ref><ref>[http://www.auto-motor-und-sport.de/eco/elektroauto-rinspeed-uc-auf-dem-genfer-autosalon-1565111.html Super-Mini mit Elektroantrieb - Rinspeed UC auf dem Genfer Autosalon] auto-motor-und-sport.de, vom 16. Dezember 2009</ref>\n* [[Rinspeed BamBoo|BamBoo]] (2011)\n* Rinspeed Dock+Go (2012)<ref>[http://www.rinspeed.eu/concept-galery.php?cid=1 Dock+Go, ein rollender Rucksack f\u00fcr Kleinfahrzeuge]</ref>\n* Rinspeed MicroMax (2013)<ref>[http://www.auto-motor-und-sport.de/news/rinspeed-micromax-auf-dem-autosalon-genf-2013-mein-e-bus-ist-dein-e-bus-6297744.html MicroMax f\u00fcr urbanen Verkehr mit Schwarm-Intelligenz]</ref>\n* Rinspeed Etos (2016)<ref>[http://www.rinspeed.eu/aktuelles.php?aid=17 Selbstfahrendes Concept Car \"Etos\"]</ref>\n* Rinspeed Oasis (2017)<ref>{{cite web|title=Rinspeed \u2013 Creative think tank for the automotive industry. Where the future is reality \u2013 today.|periodical=www.rinspeed.eu|url=http://www.rinspeed.eu/aktuelles.php?aid=20|accessdate=2016-10-10|last=Rinspeed AG}}</ref><ref>{{citation|periodical=N24.de|title=Rollender Garten: Rinspeed Oasis: Stadt-Studie f\u00fcr die CES 2017  - N24.de|language=German|url=http://www.n24.de/n24/Nachrichten/Auto-Verkehr/d/9248246/rinspeed-oasis--stadt-studie-fuer-die-ces-2017-.html|access-date=2016-10-10\n}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===zaZen===\nRinspeed zaZen is a [[Rinspeed]] [[concept car]] shown for the first time at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2006|2006 Geneva Motor Show]]. It is based on the [[Porsche 911]] ([[Porsche 997|997]]) Carrera&nbsp;S platform and developed in collaboration with [[Bayer]] MaterialScience.\n\nThe zaZen is powered by a [[flat-6]] engine that has a displacement of {{convert|3824|cc}} and develops a maximum power of 355 bhp (261 kW) at 6600 rpm. The car is able to accelerate from 0 to 60 mph in 4.8 seconds and reach a top speed of 182&nbsp;mph (293 km/h).<ref>{{cite web|title=2006 Rinspeed Zazen|url=http://www.topspeed.com/cars/rinspeed/2006-rinspeed-zazen-ar2242.html|website=topspeed.com|accessdate=January 1, 2017|date=February 2, 2006}}</ref>\n===sQuba===\n{{Main|Rinspeed sQuba}}\nBuilt around a [[Lotus Elise]], the [[Rinspeed sQuba]] is a concept car that can 'fly' underwater and has zero emissions. It debuted at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2008|2008 Geneva Motor Show]], 30 years after its inspiration: the movie ''[[The Spy Who Loved Me (film)|The Spy Who Loved Me]]''. The sQuba was featured in the first episode of 14th season of UK motoring show ''[[Fifth Gear]]''.\n\n===Splash===\n[[File:Rinspeed Splash (MIAS).JPG|thumb|Rinspeed Splash photographed at the 2009 Montreal International Auto Show]] \nThe Rinspeed Splash is a concept [[amphibious vehicle|amphibian vehicle]] with [[hydrofoil]] design capable of 45 [[knot (unit)|knots]] on water or nearly {{Convert|200|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} on land. Propelled by a 750 cc two cylinder [[turbocharger|turbo-charged]] [[engine]] burning [[methane|natural gas]] which supplies {{convert|140|hp|abbr=on|0}} at 7000 rpm and weighs just {{convert|825|kg|abbr=on|0}}, this strange-looking vehicle can accelerate from 0 to 100&nbsp;km/h in 5.9 seconds. It premiered at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2004|2004 Geneva Motor Show]]. The Splash was featured in an episode of ''[[Top Gear (current format)|Top Gear]]''. In 2006 it set a record for crossing the [[English Channel]] in a hydrofoil car, making the journey in 3 hours 14 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|author=Stuart Waterman |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2006/07/27/rinspeed-splash-sets-english-channel-record/ |title=Rinspeed \"Splash\" sets English Channel record |publisher=Autoblog |date=2006-07-27 |accessdate=2013-10-20}}</ref>\n\n===iChange===\n[[File:Rinspeed iChange.JPG|thumb|Rinspeed iChange April 2009|alt=]] \nThe iChange is a concept car that changes shape and configuration based on the number of passengers inside, up to three. It was unveiled at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2009|2009 Geneva Motor Show]]. The car features are controlled by an [[Apple iPhone]] and it is powered by a {{convert|150|kW|abbr=on|0}} electric motor. The iChange has a 0\u2013100&nbsp;km/h (62&nbsp;mph) speed of slightly over four seconds, and can hit a top speed of {{convert|136|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.automoblog.net/2009/02/19/rinspeed-ichange-concept/|title=Rinspeed iChange Concept - A Shapeshifting Electric Car|publisher=Automoblog.net}}</ref>\n\n===UC===\nThe Rinspeed UC is a micro concept electric car that was presented at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2010|2010 Geneva Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcarfans.com/109121623572/rinspeed-uc-electric-vehicle-concept-set-for-debut-in-geneva|title=RINSPEED UC Electric Vehicle Concept Set for Debut in Geneva|publisher=worldcarfans.com}}</ref> The name UC stands for \"Urban Commuter\" or \"You see\". It is a 2.5 metres long micro vehicle, operated with a central joystick. The electric motor delivers {{convert|124|Nm|abbr=on|0}} of torque. The concept car can reach a top speed of {{convert|110|km/h|abbr=on|0}}, and on-board batteries enable the car a capable of {{convert|120|km|abbr=on|0}} range in one charge.\n\n===Budii===\n[[File:2015-03-03 Geneva Motor Show 4007.JPG|thumb|Rinspeed Budii at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2015|2015 Geneva Motor Show]]|alt=]] \nThe Budii concept displayed at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2015|2015 Geneva Motor Show]] is worked around the future possibilities of self driven cars. Budii displays experiments to include vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) and vehicle-to-infrastructure (V2X) radio-based communications, radar and motion sensing systems including advanced camera monitoring. It is also equipped with telescoping laser scanner on the roof called TrackView which can be raised by 70 centimeters and delivers a precise 3D perspective by combining data from all the various sensors to map the surrounding terrain. <ref>{{cite news|title=Rinspeed Budii Concept Revealed Ahead Of 2015 Geneva Motor Show|url=http://www.motorauthority.com/news/1096838_rinspeed-budii-concept-revealed-ahead-of-2015-geneva-motor-show-video|accessdate=19 February 2015|publisher=Motorauthority}}</ref>\n\n=== \u01a9tos===\n[[File:2016-03-01 Geneva Motor Show G135.JPG|thumb|\u01a9tos in the [[Geneva Motor Show]] 2016]] \nConcept \u01a9tos is a concept presented in the [[Consumer Electronics Show]] in 2016. It is based on the [[BMW i8]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hofacker |first1=Angelina |title=Rinspeed zeigt neue Fahrzeugstudie Etos mit Drohne an Bord |url=https://www.springerprofessional.de/en/automobil---motoren/automatisiertes-fahren/rinspeed-zeigt-neue-fahrzeugstudie-etos-mit-drohne-an-bord/7069438 |publisher=Springer Professional |accessdate=26 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Oasis===\n[[File:Rinspeed Oasis - Hannover-Messe 2017 02.jpg|thumb|Oasis in the [[Geneva Motor Show]] 2017]] \nAnnounced late in 2016 and first shown at the [[Consumer Electronics Show]] in Las Vegas in January 2017, the Rinspeed Oasis concept car takes Rinspeed's 2015 Budii and 2016 Etos concept cars farther, integrating state-of-the art autonomous vehicle technologies, social media, and [[Transportation as a Service|Mobility as a Service]] into a compact car described as a \"living room\" on wheels.<ref>[https://www.cnet.com/roadshow/pictures/the-rinspeed-oasis-concept-is-a-funky-living-room-on-wheels/ The Rinspeed Oasis concept is a funky living room on wheels], CNET.com. Retrieved February 8 2017</ref> It also features floor to ceiling glass doors, a battery-electric engine, retractable steering wheel, solar panels integrated into the roof, and an [[augmented reality]] display. An unusual feature, for a car, is the dash-mounted garden with sensors to advise the user when to feed the plants.<ref>Alistair Charlton, \"[http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/breathe-easy-this-self-driving-concept-car-has-its-own-mobile-garden-1600473 Breathe easy, this self-driving concept car has its own mobile garden], IBI Times, January 11, 2017. Retrieved February 8, 2017.</ref> It was also shown at the [[Detroit Motor Show]]. Partners on the project included [[Kostal]] (electronics), [[Harman International Industries|Harman]] (electronic controls), [[WayRay]] (infotainment system) among a wide range of other firms.\n\n==Modified / tuned cars==\n*In 1993, Rinspeed modified a [[Dodge Viper (SR I)|Dodge Viper]] with electronically controlled nitrous injection and various other modifications to create the [[Rinspeed Veleno]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rinspeed.eu/en/Veleno_44_concept-car.html#mehrlesen|title=Rinspeed AG - Creative think tank for the automotive industry. Where the future is reality \u2013 today.|website=www.rinspeed.eu|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n*In 2005, Rinspeed modified a [[Subaru Forester]] to make it appear more feminine - [https://web.archive.org/web/20061211011336/http://www.subaru-presse.de/frauundauto2005/ForesterLady2006.htm Forester Lady 2006]\n*In 2007, Rinspeed offered a modified [[Porsche 911|997]] [[Porsche 911#997 Turbo|911 Turbo]] that has been transformed into a [[Le Mans 600]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rinspeed.eu Rinspeed Official site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110624061352/http://www.midnighttracks.net/2009/pageiaa-13 Rinspeed Editorial Video]; West Coast Midnight Run, Vol. 2009, The International Frankfurt Automotive Show\n{{commonscat|Rinspeed vehicles}}\n{{Automotive industry in Switzerland}}\n[[Category:Auto parts suppliers of Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Swiss brands]]\n[[Category:Automotive motorsports and performance companies]]\n[[Category:Rinspeed vehicles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Primary sources|date=February 2008}}\n[[File:Rinspeed Logo.jpg|thumb|right|400px|Rinspeed Logo]]\n\n'''Rinspeed''' is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[List of automobile manufacturers|automobile manufacturer]] and [[Car tuning|tuning]] designer. It specialises in restoring classic cars, and tuning and modifying modern cars such as [[Porsche]]s and [[Subaru]]s.  Since 1991, they have also designed exotic [[concept car|concept]] and special vehicles for the [[Geneva Motor Show]] and other car shows each year, but do not enter into production.\n\nRinspeed was founded in 1979 by Frank Rinderknecht.\n\n==Concept cars==\n[[File:Rinspeed sQuba (TWB 2008).jpg|thumb|sQuba concept car at the Tuning World Bodensee 2008]] \n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* [[Rinspeed Speed-Art|Speed-Art]] (1992)\n* [[Rinspeed Veleno|Veleno]] (1993)\n* Cyan (1994)\n* Roadster R + SC-R (1995)\n* [[Rinspeed Yello Talbo|Yello Talbo]] (1996)\n* [[Rinspeed Mono Ego|Mono Ego]] (1997)\n* E-Go Rocket (1998)\n* X-Trem (1999)\n* [[Rinspeed Tatooo.com|Tatooo.com]] (2000)\n* [[Rinspeed Rone|R<sup>one</sup>]] (2001)\n* [[Rinspeed Presto|Presto]] (2002)\n* [[Rinspeed Bedouin|Bedouin]] (2003)\n* [[Rinspeed Splash|Splash]] (2004)\n* Chopster (2005)\n* [[Rinspeed Senso|Senso]] (2005)\n* [[Rinspeed zaZen|zaZen]] (2006)\n* [[Rinspeed eXasis|eXasis]] (2007)\n* [[Rinspeed Le Mans 600|Le Mans 600]]\n* [[Rinspeed sQuba|sQuba]] (2008)\n* [[Rinspeed iChange|iChange]] (2009)\n* [[Rinspeed UC?|UC?]] (2010)<ref>{{Webarchiv | url=http://www.rinspeed.com/pages/cars/uc/prd-uc.htm | wayback=20110612082015 | text=Rinspeed vereint Auto, Bahn und Web in einem neuartigen Mobilit\u00e4tskonzept}} (Herstellerseite)</ref><ref>[http://www.auto-motor-und-sport.de/eco/elektroauto-rinspeed-uc-auf-dem-genfer-autosalon-1565111.html Super-Mini mit Elektroantrieb - Rinspeed UC auf dem Genfer Autosalon] auto-motor-und-sport.de, vom 16. Dezember 2009</ref>\n* [[Rinspeed BamBoo|BamBoo]] (2011)\n* Rinspeed Dock+Go (2012)<ref>[http://www.rinspeed.eu/concept-galery.php?cid=1 Dock+Go, ein rollender Rucksack f\u00fcr Kleinfahrzeuge]</ref>\n* Rinspeed MicroMax (2013)<ref>[http://www.auto-motor-und-sport.de/news/rinspeed-micromax-auf-dem-autosalon-genf-2013-mein-e-bus-ist-dein-e-bus-6297744.html MicroMax f\u00fcr urbanen Verkehr mit Schwarm-Intelligenz]</ref>\n* Rinspeed Etos (2016)<ref>[http://www.rinspeed.eu/aktuelles.php?aid=17 Selbstfahrendes Concept Car \"Etos\"]</ref>\n* Rinspeed Oasis (2017)<ref>{{cite web|title=Rinspeed \u2013 Creative think tank for the automotive industry. Where the future is reality \u2013 today.|periodical=www.rinspeed.eu|url=http://www.rinspeed.eu/aktuelles.php?aid=20|accessdate=2016-10-10|last=Rinspeed AG}}</ref><ref>{{citation|periodical=N24.de|title=Rollender Garten: Rinspeed Oasis: Stadt-Studie f\u00fcr die CES 2017  - N24.de|language=German|url=http://www.n24.de/n24/Nachrichten/Auto-Verkehr/d/9248246/rinspeed-oasis--stadt-studie-fuer-die-ces-2017-.html|access-date=2016-10-10\n}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===zaZen===\nRinspeed zaZen is a [[Rinspeed]] [[concept car]] shown for the first time at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2006|2006 Geneva Motor Show]]. It is based on the [[Porsche 911]] ([[Porsche 997|997]]) Carrera&nbsp;S platform and developed in collaboration with [[Bayer]] MaterialScience.\n\nThe zaZen is powered by a [[flat-6]] engine that has a displacement of {{convert|3824|cc}} and develops a maximum power of 355 bhp (261 kW) at 6600 rpm. The car is able to accelerate from 0 to 60 mph in 4.8 seconds and reach a top speed of 182&nbsp;mph (293 km/h).<ref>{{cite web|title=2006 Rinspeed Zazen|url=http://www.topspeed.com/cars/rinspeed/2006-rinspeed-zazen-ar2242.html|website=topspeed.com|accessdate=January 1, 2017|date=February 2, 2006}}</ref>\n===sQuba===\n{{Main|Rinspeed sQuba}}\nBuilt around a [[Lotus Elise]], the [[Rinspeed sQuba]] is a concept car that can 'fly' underwater and has zero emissions. It debuted at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2008|2008 Geneva Motor Show]], 30 years after its inspiration: the movie ''[[The Spy Who Loved Me (film)|The Spy Who Loved Me]]''. The sQuba was featured in the first episode of 14th season of UK motoring show ''[[Fifth Gear]]''.\n\n===Splash===\n[[File:Rinspeed Splash (MIAS).JPG|thumb|Rinspeed Splash photographed at the 2009 Montreal International Auto Show]] \nThe Rinspeed Splash is a concept [[amphibious vehicle|amphibian vehicle]] with [[hydrofoil]] design capable of 45 [[knot (unit)|knots]] on water or nearly {{Convert|200|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} on land. Propelled by a 750 cc two cylinder [[turbocharger|turbo-charged]] [[engine]] burning [[methane|natural gas]] which supplies {{convert|140|hp|abbr=on|0}} at 7000 rpm and weighs just {{convert|825|kg|abbr=on|0}}, this strange-looking vehicle can accelerate from 0 to 100&nbsp;km/h in 5.9 seconds. It premiered at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2004|2004 Geneva Motor Show]]. The Splash was featured in an episode of ''[[Top Gear (current format)|Top Gear]]''. In 2006 it set a record for crossing the [[English Channel]] in a hydrofoil car, making the journey in 3 hours 14 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|author=Stuart Waterman |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2006/07/27/rinspeed-splash-sets-english-channel-record/ |title=Rinspeed \"Splash\" sets English Channel record |publisher=Autoblog |date=2006-07-27 |accessdate=2013-10-20}}</ref>\n\n===iChange===\n[[File:Rinspeed iChange.JPG|thumb|Rinspeed iChange April 2009|alt=]] \nThe iChange is a concept car that changes shape and configuration based on the number of passengers inside, up to three. It was unveiled at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2009|2009 Geneva Motor Show]]. The car features are controlled by an [[Apple iPhone]] and it is powered by a {{convert|150|kW|abbr=on|0}} electric motor. The iChange has a 0\u2013100&nbsp;km/h (62&nbsp;mph) speed of slightly over four seconds, and can hit a top speed of {{convert|136|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.automoblog.net/2009/02/19/rinspeed-ichange-concept/|title=Rinspeed iChange Concept - A Shapeshifting Electric Car|publisher=Automoblog.net}}</ref>\n\n===UC===\nThe Rinspeed UC is a micro concept electric car that was presented at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2010|2010 Geneva Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcarfans.com/109121623572/rinspeed-uc-electric-vehicle-concept-set-for-debut-in-geneva|title=RINSPEED UC Electric Vehicle Concept Set for Debut in Geneva|publisher=worldcarfans.com}}</ref> The name UC stands for \"Urban Commuter\" or \"You see\". It is a 2.5 metres long micro vehicle, operated with a central joystick. The electric motor delivers {{convert|124|Nm|abbr=on|0}} of torque. The concept car can reach a top speed of {{convert|110|km/h|abbr=on|0}}, and on-board batteries enable the car a capable of {{convert|120|km|abbr=on|0}} range in one charge.\n\n===Budii===\n[[File:2015-03-03 Geneva Motor Show 4007.JPG|thumb|Rinspeed Budii at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2015|2015 Geneva Motor Show]]|alt=]] \nThe Budii concept displayed at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2015|2015 Geneva Motor Show]] is worked around the future possibilities of self driven cars. Budii displays experiments to include vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) and vehicle-to-infrastructure (V2X) radio-based communications, radar and motion sensing systems including advanced camera monitoring. It is also equipped with telescoping laser scanner on the roof called TrackView which can be raised by 70 centimeters and delivers a precise 3D perspective by combining data from all the various sensors to map the surrounding terrain. <ref>{{cite news|title=Rinspeed Budii Concept Revealed Ahead Of 2015 Geneva Motor Show|url=http://www.motorauthority.com/news/1096838_rinspeed-budii-concept-revealed-ahead-of-2015-geneva-motor-show-video|accessdate=19 February 2015|publisher=Motorauthority}}</ref>\n\n=== \u01a9tos===\n[[File:2016-03-01 Geneva Motor Show G135.JPG|thumb|\u01a9tos in the [[Geneva Motor Show]] 2016]] \nConcept \u01a9tos is a concept presented in the [[Consumer Electronics Show]] in 2016. It is based on the [[BMW i8]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hofacker |first1=Angelina |title=Rinspeed zeigt neue Fahrzeugstudie Etos mit Drohne an Bord |url=https://www.springerprofessional.de/en/automobil---motoren/automatisiertes-fahren/rinspeed-zeigt-neue-fahrzeugstudie-etos-mit-drohne-an-bord/7069438 |publisher=Springer Professional |accessdate=26 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Oasis===\n[[File:Rinspeed Oasis - Hannover-Messe 2017 02.jpg|thumb|Oasis in the [[Geneva Motor Show]] 2017]] \nAnnounced late in 2016 and first shown at the [[Consumer Electronics Show]] in Las Vegas in January 2017, the Rinspeed Oasis concept car takes Rinspeed's 2015 Budii and 2016 Etos concept cars farther, integrating state-of-the art autonomous vehicle technologies, social media, and [[Transportation as a Service|Mobility as a Service]] into a compact car described as a \"living room\" on wheels.<ref>[https://www.cnet.com/roadshow/pictures/the-rinspeed-oasis-concept-is-a-funky-living-room-on-wheels/ The Rinspeed Oasis concept is a funky living room on wheels], CNET.com. Retrieved February 8 2017</ref> It also features floor to ceiling glass doors, a battery-electric engine, retractable steering wheel, solar panels integrated into the roof, and an [[augmented reality]] display. An unusual feature, for a car, is the dash-mounted garden with sensors to advise the user when to feed the plants.<ref>Alistair Charlton, \"[http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/breathe-easy-this-self-driving-concept-car-has-its-own-mobile-garden-1600473 Breathe easy, this self-driving concept car has its own mobile garden], IBI Times, January 11, 2017. Retrieved February 8, 2017.</ref> It was also shown at the [[Detroit Motor Show]]. Partners on the project included [[Kostal]] (electronics), [[Harman International Industries|Harman]] (electronic controls), [[WayRay]] (infotainment system) among a wide range of other firms.\n\n==Modified / tuned cars==\n*In 1993, Rinspeed modified a [[Dodge Viper (SR I)|Dodge Viper]] with electronically controlled nitrous injection and various other modifications to create the [[Rinspeed Veleno]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rinspeed.eu/en/Veleno_44_concept-car.html#mehrlesen|title=Rinspeed AG - Creative think tank for the automotive industry. Where the future is reality \u2013 today.|website=www.rinspeed.eu|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n*In 2005, Rinspeed modified a [[Subaru Forester]] to make it appear more feminine - [https://web.archive.org/web/20061211011336/http://www.subaru-presse.de/frauundauto2005/ForesterLady2006.htm Forester Lady 2006]\n*In 2007, Rinspeed offered a modified [[Porsche 911|997]] [[Porsche 911#997 Turbo|911 Turbo]] that has been transformed into a [[Le Mans 600]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rinspeed.eu Rinspeed Official site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110624061352/http://www.midnighttracks.net/2009/pageiaa-13 Rinspeed Editorial Video]; West Coast Midnight Run, Vol. 2009, The International Frankfurt Automotive Show\n{{commonscat|Rinspeed vehicles}}\n{{Automotive industry in Switzerland}}\n[[Category:Auto parts suppliers of Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Swiss brands]]\n[[Category:Automotive motorsports and performance companies]]\n[[Category:Rinspeed vehicles]]\n", "name_user": "TKOIII", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eConcept cars:year", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rinspeed"}
